Todd Jasper wrote:

 Hey guys,

      Just thought I'd share something I learned and wanted to hear what you
guys think about it. I just got back from a trip to Holland. I always look
at the cars any time I leave the US and I noticed I didn't see very many VW
Busses at all. As a matter of fact, I believe i only saw two the entire time
I was there, and they were both Bay Busses.

 Anyone have any opinions on this?

 On a side note, I did see literally THOUSANDS of what we call "EuroVans".
In Holland however, they were all titled as "Transporter"... which I thought
was kind of cool. The EuroVan over there seemed to have been used just like
hte VW Bus was back in the day... there were some panel vans, some camper
vans, some pickup truck vans... etc...

 As someone else on here mentioned, the EuroVans that I saw which were
camper vans, were not done by Westfalia. If they were, it didn't say it on
there.
